        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">---I've edited the title of this post to better describe the situation and possibly get more attention from readers of this board.---</P><P>I've checked and rechecked, and I'm absolutely certain, beyond any and all doubt, that the lvl 44 pet is not healing when it's lifetap proc goes off.</P><P>First, and most obviously, only the mob staggers. If you've ever seen a lifetap spell, you know that both the caster and target stagger.</P><P>I figured that it was possible that these lifetaps were different, so I simply spammed /pet health report after every proc. Even if the pet was only healing 10 hp per proc, it should be getting 1 percent back, unless the 45 hitter has over 1000 hp.</P><P>Well, after getting multiple procs in a row for several rounds, the pet didn't regain even 1 percent. I suppose it's possible that the pet only heals 1 hp per proc, but then there's no reason to even have it.</P><P>What I guess I'm saying is that I want someone to do what I've done: Test it for yourself, and when you come to the same conclusion, do a /bug repot. Maybe they'll fix it in a year... /shrug</P><P>---This sig will no longer drop in game.---</P><P>Edited by - Nennayan on 10/09/2001  18:34:54</font></td>
